Weather App with Django
1. Language: Python, HTML, CSS
2. Framework: Django
3. API: Use OpenWeather API to get the weather of cities including current weather and forecast weather with every 3-hour interval.
4. How to start the project 
 a. Use terminal to go to the project folder (weather_project)
 b. Type python manage.py runserver
 c. Copy this URL http://127.0.0.1:8000/ to start 
5. You can type 1 or 2 cities and it will show the current weather and forecast weather with every 3-hour interval.  
